<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
 *Mirage Resorts rose 1 15/16 to 20 11/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	Operating income was 20 cents a share, well below analysts'  
estimated 28 cents a share. However, Mirage said its new Bellagio 
resort generated $244 million in revenues, or $3 million each day, 
during the 77 days it was open in the fourth quarter. NationsBanc 
Montgomery and BT Alex Brown upgraded the stock. 

</P>
<P>
 *Lubrizol Corp. fell 13/16 to 19 3/16.  
</P>
<P>
 *General Electric Co. rose 3 5/8 to 104. 
</P>
<P>
	The companies agreed to jointly develop, make and market  
products and services for diesel-electric powered locomotives and 
off-highway vehicles. 

</P>
<P>
 *Pinkerton Inc. rose 11 11/16 to 28 9/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The security provider is being acquired by Securitas AB of  
Sweden for $384 million in a deal they say will create the world's 
largest full-service security company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Lucent Technologies rose 3 1/2 to 106 1/2.    	
</P>
<P>
	Lucent's microelectronics group unit acquired Sybarus  
Technologies of Ottawa, Ontario, a privately held semiconductor 
design company. The deal gives Lucent integrated circuit technology 
for its data and telecommunications transmission systems. 

</P>
<P>
 *Gateway 2000 rose 6 7/16 to 79 5/16.  
</P>
<P>
 *Advanced Micro Devices rose 1 11/16 to 19 5/16. 
</P>
<P>
 *Intel shares rose 4 3/4 to 132 13/16. 
</P>
<P>
	AMD unveiled a new microprocessor for desktop personal computers  
designed to challened Intel's new Pentium III chips. Meanwhile, 
Gateway selected AMD as its second supplier of microprocessor 
components after Intel. Piper Jaffray upgraded Gateway. Hambricht &AMP; 
Quist started coverage of Gateway with a buy rating. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Rambus rose 9 5/8 to 80 5/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	BancBoston Robertson Stevens upgraded the maker of high-speed  
computer memory technology, and Warburg Dillon Read started 
coverage at a strong buy. 

</P>
<P>
 *Room Plus rose 7/8 to 2 1/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company plans to launch an online interactive shopping  
service to sell its modular, mica-laminated furniture to 
residential users. 

</P>
</TEXT>
