<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 10; Nasdag Is Up 11 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened narrowly higher. The  
Dow Jones Industrial Average is up ten points in today's early 
going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 4-3 lead 
over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up eleven points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up one point. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street is expected to get off to a slow start to the  
trading week. 
</P>
<P>
	There's been talk of some apprehension in the market, ahead of  
Federal Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan's congressional testimony 
tomorrow. 
</P>
<P>
	At the same time, a flurry of activity in the mergers and  
acquisitions arena should spark some market movement. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the items -- Dominion Resources' purchase of Consolidated  
Natural Gas and Sempra Energy's acquisition of KN Energy. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, United Technologies is buying Sundstrand.  
</P>
<P>
	And in Italy, Olivetti is bidding to buy Telecom Italia.  


