<HEADLINE> Angels To Play Mexican Team April 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- The Anaheim Angels will play an  
exhibition game against the Aguascalientes Railroadmen of the 
Mexican League on April 3 at Edison International Field. 
</P>
<P>
	It will mark the first time ever that a Mexican League team will  
face a major league team in a big league ballpark. It will also be 
the final exhibition game for the Angels, who open the season April 
6 against Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	Aguascalientes opens its season March 17 and will have played 15  
regular-season games before meeting the Angels. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've enjoyed a mutually beneficial relationship with  
Aguascalientes in recent years, and we're excited to give them a 
chance to play in a major league facility like Edison Field,'' 
Angels general manager Bill Bavasi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
