<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Avalanche Recall Goaltender Denis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- The Colorado Avalanche recalled goaltender Marc  
Denis from the club's AHL affiliate on Monday, a day after starter 
Patrick Roy suffered a groin injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Roy was hurt in Sunday's 1-1 tie against the Dallas Stars. His  
condition was listed as day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	Denis was first recalled from the Hershey Bears this season on  
Dec. 26. He appeared in four games for the Avalanche and posted a 
1-1-1 record in three early-January starts. 
</P>
<P>
	The Avalanche host the Vancouver Canucks on Tuesday night.  
</P>
