<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Levi Strauss To Slash 5,900 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Levi Strauss &AMP; Co. will close 11 of its 22  
plants in North America and lay off about 5,900 employees, or 30 
percent of its work force in the United States and Canada, as the 
jeans maker struggles with slumping sales. 
</P>
<P>
	The San Francisco-based company said it will shift production to  
plants overseas, which will enable it to spend more time and money 
on product design and marketing, two areas where it has been 
lagging in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales at Levi Strauss fell 13 percent last year to $6 billion.  
It was the second year of disappointing results at the privately 
held company, which doesn't release earnings reports or any 
competitive data on specific business units or brands. 
</P>
<P>
	Levi's business has been under pressure as it competes with  
well-known labels from the Gap and Tommy Hilfiger, newcomers like 
MUDD and JNCO and lower-priced jeans from Sears and Wal-Mart. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's announcement is just the latest round of cutbacks at the  
San Francisco-based company. Starting in late 1997, it laid off 
7,400 workers, more than a third of its North American workforce, 
and closed more than 10 plants, not counting the cuts announced 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	``Levi's is less and less able to compete with everyone else in  
this business,'' said Kurt Barnard, a retail consultant and 
president of Barnard's Retail Trend Report in Upper Montclair, N.J. 
``There jeans just aren't in demand like they used to be.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Levi's will close 10 U.S. plants and one in Ontario, Canada.  
Four plants in Texas will close, two in Tennessee, one in Georgia, 
one in Arkansas, one in Virginia, and one in North Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
	Levi's will be offering benefits packages to U.S. employees that  
include three weeks of severance pay for each year of service, 
extended medical coverage and up to $6,000 towards training, 
education and business start-up expenses. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
