<HEADLINE> Mercedes-Benz Recalls Cabriolets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTVALE, N.J. (AP) -- Mercedes-Benz of North America Inc. will  
recall about 2,600 CLK convertible coupes sold in the United States 
to reinforce the front shoulder belts, which could pull loose in a 
major collision, the luxury car maker said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mercedes-Benz of North America wrote letters to owners who  
bought the cars offering to install specially designed anchor bolt 
assemblies to correct the problem. The letters asked owners to take 
their cars to the nearest dealer for the free repair. 
</P>
<P>
	Mercedes-Benz detected the problem during a quality-control  
inspection of the two-door, four-seat CLK30 convertibles. It said 
it has received no reports of the belts failing during actual use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
